!!! The Great Tower

The Great Tower is a fortress within a fortress. The area is accessible via the wall top doors (usually locked) or the courtyard staircase that leads up to the drawbridge (area 18 on the [[Harken Keep]] map). The drawbridge is normally down (open) but can be raised at the first sign of trouble.

Eight of the ten sentries in this encounter are stationed atop the adjoining east and southeast walls (see the map in the <<scrollToHeader "Wall Defense">> encounter). The other two sentries are inside the keep, guarding the drawbridge. 

When Arien approaches the tower, read:

<<<
//The castle's great tower stands nearly 60 feet tall. No doors open to the ground of the upper bailey; instead, an exposed stairway leads up to a second-story drawbridge. Several arrow slits look out over the courtyard.//
<<<

When Arien enters area 23, the foyer, read:

<<<
//This grand hallway is 20 feet high, with old coats of arms and banners displayed proudly. A large double door stands across the drawbridge, and several smaller doors appear in other walls. A windlass mechanism controls the drawbridge. A pair of [[Iron Circle]] soldiers wearing black surcoats embroidered with a red-trimmed gray circle guard this hallway.//
<<<

If Arien acts quickly, or successfully bluffs or sneaks her way through, she may be able to rush the tower's front hall before the drawbridge can be closed. If Arien is stuck outside the tower, the Iron Circle soldiers attack from whichever arrow slit or parapet is convenient. The sentries on the southeast wall have a good shot at someone standing on the top landing of the exterior staircase.

The sentries on the adjoining wall tops hold their positions and fire at characters outside the tower until Arien and all her allies are inside the tower. Then the sentries move into the tower to join the fighting inside.

If combat erupts on this level of the keep, the villains on the levels above and below are alerted. They remain in their designated areas and cannot be surprised.

!!! The Gaol

This encounter takes place on the first floor of the Great Tower (areas 19 and 22 in particular, on the [[Harken Keep]] map). [[Nazin Redthorn]] has assigned two enforcers (wearing chain mail, one has a flail, the other a sword) to make sure that [[Jonn Stockmer]] stays put in the dungeons of his own castle. A [[wandslinger]] (who actually wields a staff and doesn't do the fiery tendrils thing, but can cast [[eldritch blast]] and [[acid arrow]]) and a [[tar devil]] (which wields a kukri and can fling balls of hot pitch) round out the guard detail. They also keep an eye on the nearby postern gate (area 21) and supervise the few remaining castle servants working in the kitchen.

When Arien enters area 19, read:

<<<
//This area is the Great Tower's kitchen. Several pots hang over a large hearth, and counters full of supplies and utensils line the walls. A stairway climbs up to the foyer, and a postern gate leads outside to the castle. Servants work in the kitchen, cowering before a brawny Iron Circle soldier who's keeping an eye on them. [if coming down the stairs] A heavy, reinforced door beyond the hearth opens to a small guardroom where an Iron Circle soldier sits playing a card game with a bearded mage.//
<<<

When infiltrators appear on the stairs or at the postern gate, the soldier in the kitchen moves to guard the doorway leading to the gaol (area 22) and calls for help. The second soldier comes out to defend the doorway; the mage and [[tar devil]] hang back and use ranged attacks.

If the fight goes badly, the mage seals himself in the gaol guardroom, possibly locking the soldiers outside. The mage threatens to kill [[Stockmer|Jonn Stockmer]] unless Arien agrees to let him flee. This is an empty threat, since the mage would never slay the castellan without Nazin's approval; Arien might realize this is a bluff if she's insightful.

The castle servants are loyal Harkenwolders forced into drudgery by the [[Iron Circle]]. They do their best to stay out of the way and shout encouragement at the heroes. They tell Arien that Stockmer is being held in a cell beyond the guardroom. See [[Jonn Stockmer]] for notes on what the castellan can tell the heroes upon being rescued.

!!! The Count's Chambers

[[Nazin Redthorn]], the would-be lord of [[Harkenwold]], makes his lair in the rooms formerly belonging to Count [[ir'Clarn|Alben ir'Clarn]] and Castellan [[Stockmer|Jonn Stockmer]]. Attending him are three loyal [[hobgoblin]] bodyguards (wielding morningstars and backup daggers) and an infernal wandslinger (fiery tendrils, dark imperative). If Nazin did not survive the Battle of Mistmarsh, replace him with a different Iron Circle commander named Tyranda Falkon.

If the heroes come up the secret stairs from area 26, they might surprise Nazin and his guards.

When (if) Arien enters area 27, read:

<<<
//A sitting room opens at the top of the stairs. At the far end stands a large door emblazoned with the Clarn coat of arms. Two fierce [[hobgoblin]] warriors in scale armor glare at you and raise their morningstars.//
<<<

When entering area 30, read (adjusting if Nazin is not present):

<<<
//This spacious suite clearly belongs to the master of the keep. Comfortable carpets cover the wooden floor, and various tapestries and paintings hang on the walls. Across the room stands a large canopy bed. A magnificent hearth lies in a corner. A hobgoblin with a morningstar stands guard by the door, and standing over a table is a priest in Iron Circle scarlet. Sitting near him is a tall, massively muscled man with short red hair and a great three-headed flail at his side—[[Nazin Redthorn]]!//

//The warlord of the Iron Circle looks at you with contempt. "You think you've defeated us?" he snarls. "You are a rabbit in the wolf's den. We'll hang your corpse from the battlements!"//
<<<

The hobgoblins in area 27 roar as they rush boldly into melee. Nazin and the others in area 30 hear the fighting outside and get ready to join the battle. Nazin is likely to come out of the room to take the fight to Arien.

Nazin swings his flail expertly, perhaps trying to sweep Arien's legs out. He also may use his infernal flames ([[burning hands]]). 

The wandslinger stays out of melee reach and uses fiery tendrils. He reserves his dark imperative (extra defense and adding [[necrotic damage|damage type]] to attacks) for Nazin, using it to aid the warlord when he's injured.

If the battle turns against Nazin, he orders his remaining followers to hold off the heroes for as long as possible and attempts to flee down the secret staircase down to area 26. He first tries to gather reinforcements, but if there are none, he heads down to the gaol to murder Stockmer out of sheer anger and spite.

!! Conclusion

After Arien defeats [[Nazin Redthorn]], free Stockmer, and rid [[Harken Keep]] of villains and monsters, the [[Iron Circle]] is decisively defeated. Stockmer orders messages be sent to Count Alben and the [[King's Citadel]], and militia members arrest bribed [[Municipal Guards|Breland Municipal Guard]]. Any surviving mercenaries abroad in [[Harkenwold]] soon realize that the tide has turned against them and beat a hasty retreat east, possibly into [[Darguun]]. They won't be back anytime soon.

Arien is hailed throughout Harkenwold as a great hero. She's treated as an honored guest in the keep and the villages. Count Alben, when he arrives from Wroat (after 6 days; he takes a carriage that travels along the Orien trade road with the help of a [[Mark of Passage]], but it's still 500 miles of road), confers an honorary title on Arien: Defender of Harkenwold. (He does not have the authority to knight her.) She is also granted some reward, to be determined.

Arien gains 1 [[experience point]] at the end of this adventure. 